Q_NAME: First non-repeating character in a stream
Q_DESC:
Given an input stream of n characters consisting only of small case alphabets,the task is to find the first non repeating character each time a character is inserted to the stream by using a queue of characters.For example, In a flow of stream : a, a, b, c

a goes to stream : 1st non repeating element : a (a)
a goes to stream : no non repeating element: 0 (a, a)
b goes to stream: 1st non repeating element: b (a, a, b)
c goes to stream : 1st non repeating element: b(a, a, b, c)

INPUT:

The first line of input contains an integer T denoting the no of test cases.Then,T test cases follow. Each test case contains an integer N denoting the size of the stream. Then, in the next line are the characters which are inserted to the stream.

OUTPUT:

For each test case in a new line print the first non repeating elements separated by spaces present in the stream at every instinct when a character is added to the stream, if no such element is present print 0.
